<subSubSection pageNumber="831" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="831">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="831">Note:</emphasis>
Although the protologues of both this and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gouan (1764)" authorityName="Gouan" authorityYear="1764" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Tragopogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="831">Tragopogon hirsutus</emphasis>
Gouan (1764)
</taxonomicName>
are not identical, and despite Linnaeus making no reference to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gouan’s">Gouan's</normalizedToken>
publication, Art. 33.3 allows 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="831">S. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be interpreted as a new combination based on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gouan’s">Gouan's</normalizedToken>
name. If this interpretation is adopted, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gouan) L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" baseAuthorityName="Gouan" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scorzonera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="831">S. hirsuta</emphasis>
(Gouan) L.
</taxonomicName>
is apparently untypified.
</paragraph>
